cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on multi-label image recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also proposes a novel approach using graph convolutional networks (GCN) to model label dependencies, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper incorporates natural language processing techniques such as word embeddings to learn label correlations, which is a common topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on two diverse datasets, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) analysis.
